76561198028769894,Recommended,410670,20476522,"Posted: 11 January, 2016",all,Shuvack,"The inspirations from OFF are unmistakeable, the somewhat scribbly artstyle, unsettling music, corporate themes and the tone of oddity and deppression, even Batter and Mortis are in it, and that fact made me a bit worried about this game's subtlety.While it's a solid RPG with good amount of secrets, several hours playthrough, and an interesting atmosphere mixed with criticism of nearly any political subject (while being dirt cheap of course); it fails with its subtlety when taking on any issues or humorous references.It took me back to the time when I played OFF or Home, scratches me behind the ears with its familiar eeriness, just to straight up smack me in the face with a wooden plank when trying to jab at some society's issues not tackled by OFF previously.References are not overwhelming in numbers but astoundingly obvious, its humour is way too often the ""meme"" type of funny, and relies on making fun of actual internet/political personas, it's all incredibly not universal and very much ""here and now"", making it feel more shallow than it normally would.I'm not expecting really high level philosophical stuff from it, and I actually feel relief and joy that its tone wasn't the infamous ""capitalism is bad, all for people, it will work cause I say so"", but actually critically presented the aspects of it through the medium of its dystopian world.I'd say that I didn't wish for it to be something more, I wished for it to be something a bit less- to give away its cards with bigger hesitation, have less references to grant its world more substance and soul, something that will make me remember it for longer thanks to its intrigue.With all that said- it was really fun to play it all the way through, I'd say it's probably worth more than that one dollar, and it doesn't come off as a half a*sed RPG maker game in both art and mechanics.So the buy is very much recommended (and playing its free inspiration OFF [if you haven't and this is your style]), even if it hadn't any trading cards- it's really worth it."
