,Recommended,410670,21239422,"Posted: 15 February, 2016",all,Man Who Can Climb Anything,"TL;DR: If you hate constant internet culture jokes and references, this game is probably not for you. Otherwise, pretty good.Suits is a short RPG maker game heavily inspired by OFF. As one can see by the other reviews, the game's main selling point is its dark humor and the references it makes. The game refuses to take itself seriously all the way to the very end, and that can actually hurt the game's story at some points, even though the plot itself is pretty simple.The artstyle and the music are very unique and go along pretty well, strengthening the game's unsettling atmosphere.The gameplay is alright, but could use some improvement. There's a ton of secrets and optional events to find in every single area, which gives Suits some replay factor, but the battles are a bit too simplistic. Even though each character feels very different from the other two, the entire game can be beaten by using the same combination of 2-3 commands, only stopping every now and then to heal your party, but thankfully the game ends before this can become too repetitive.With all that said, though, this is definitely one of the most unique and interesting RPG maker games on Steam, and definitely worth every cent. I really hope to see a sequel in the future."
