,Recommended,410670,28484628,"Posted: 20 December, 2016",all,Byzantine #!nstinct,"In a NutshellCategoryScoreOverall***Graphics**Gameplay**Originality****Fun***BOTTOM OF THE BARGAIN BIN: ""Suits: A Business RPG""SummarySuits: A Business RPG is a bad game with an interesting personality. The game itself is bland. What makes Suits a fun game is the nonsensical humor within. I bought this game for ¥98 thinking it's just another poorly-made RPG that you see getting riffed on YouTube. My expectations were pleasantly surpassed.GraphicsThe graphics are deliberately♥♥♥♥♥ All the characters and objects look like a 5th grader's doodles on a notebook. It's obvious that no effort was made, literally, when everything is a scribble. The music is like outsider music, but not as bad as Crazy Bus or Dontrel Dolphin.All of it works well with the game.  The boring and uninspired art makes you feel like you're at some desk job with no clear description of what you do. It works with the drab and boring plot. It feel...businesslike.GameplayIt's an RPG Maker game. You fight, chat, and move. Combat is very simple and repetitive. I really don't have to use many special attacks to defeat the enemies, even for bosses. It feels more like doing work than playing a game.The plot is simple. You are a new hire. Suddenly, the CEO gets threatened by you and tries to kill you. Because of so many side quests, I often forget what I'm supposed to do. But the gameplay is so simple, and the area is laid out is such a linear path that I can still progress.OriginalityI have to say, I don't see many games where everything is intentionally bad. You can tell the developer didn't even try to make a game. Why would they, when everything is already made for you via RPG Maker? Instead, most of the work was spent on side quests, containing bizarre and non sequitur jokes. I would call this an unique outsider game.FunDespite all the sloppiness and half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥job this game is, it's still amusing. The humor is good and I'm always given something unexpected. It's lowbrow and juvenile humor, but it's delivered at the right time in a bland and boring game. It's ¥98 worth of fun, and it delivers on that.ClosingSuits is a weird game at the least. Is awful and stupid, but in no way is it boring. The humor is great. It's a bag of odd jokes that's tied up by a flimsy game. Is it worth the dollar? Absolutely! You have to try it to get a feel of just how the humor works so well. Good doing business with you."
76561198056606327,Recommended,410670,20514115,"Posted: 13 January, 2016",all,Carnivore,"I really enjoyed this game. For 1€, you really can't go wrong by picking this up.I advise you to watch the trailers if you're sceptical about the game in general.+ Humour+ Talking to plants+ Creative+ Quests+ Interesting coincidences+ The soundtrack is nice(especially when you meet that dinosaur, lol)+ If you love clicking on objects, you will be rewarded. If you don't enjoy it, you will after playing this game+ Subtle deeper message, that isn't shoved in your face+ Plays like a simple, oldschool, turn-based JRPG+ It took me about 4 hours to beat this game, so if you're looking for a cheap, little RPG to kill some time, definitely consider this one+ It has a feeling of a weird dev's childhood fantasy to it, which makes it really cute in my opinion+ General concept- The artstyle might not be everybody's cup of tea- I kinda found the endboss fight to be... lame- There is one sidequest where you have to wait 5 minutes and you can't be tabbed out of the game during this time frame because the ingame time won't pass otherwise- The core of this game lies at its hilarious dialogues, object interactions and humour in general. If you aren't into the game's kind of jokes, you possibly won't enjoy it- It may be a little difficult at some points, if you don't plan on fighting most of the enemies and rather skipping them- The general bossfight strategy stays the same throughout the game- Although the game's concept and story is great, it lacks in presentation at some points. You may not fully understand what's going on if you don't follow the dialogues attentively- If you are not into indie games in general, chances are you won't enjoy Suits. I've tried to come up with a better explanation for this statement, but let me just put it like that: Where Undertale is considered to be extremely ""tumblr"", Suits is tremendously ""indie""- Aside from the humour, the gameplay itself is kinda repetitive. You run around fighting enemies, buying stuff, healing yourself, talking to NPCs and plants and finding yourself in odd situations=> To recap everything I've just said:If you enjoy experimental, indie rpg games that are comical and odd in their own way, you're most likely going to enjoy Suits. If you aren't amused by it's humour and feel bored due to the gameplay, you might wanna avoid picking this up."
