,Recommended,410670,29028617,Posted: 5 January,all,Byers Hintz,"Suits: A Buisness RPG is definatly something else.  While at first glance this game just looks like a quirky game with a unique artstyle created in RPG Maker, its underlying message about corprate corruption and money in general is quite powerful. You go through the game as The Guy, (or whatever you named him I guess), on a quest to take out the C.E.O.s  of each district, fighting hobos, loan sharks, and some very out there creatures along the way. There are a ton of little side things that you can also do that really bring out this games personality, and give some replay value if you missed out along the way. The gameplay isn't too much to talk about, (again, this is an rpg maker game), and unfortunatly, there is almost no difficulty. However, it's made very clear that this game is more about the expirience itself rather than mechanics, similar to OFF, another RPG maker game, which is clearly an inspiration here. I would give this game a 7/10. I enjoyed this games humor and story from begining to end, however I do have a few complaints. First of all, as previously mentioned, this game is a cakewalk. Even if you ignore the final party member and just take Gerome, you will still most likely be fine. And while these are mostly just nitpicks, I found that the sprites really ruin the astetic of the rest of the game, and i think they should have been made in the same sketchy style everything else was done in. Lastly, and probably least importantly, overworld objects have weird detection and you can usually clip through them when walking. Other then that, i still think this is a great game. And at one dollar are you really risking anything? I would recomend Suits: A Business RPG to anyone who enjoys story driven RPGs, or just weirder ones in general."
