,Recommended,410670,20479736,"Posted: 11 January, 2016",all,Ampharosmaster64,"I convinced a friend to finally install steam just for this game. 10/10 Would seductivly slide sandwiches again.Ok in all seriousness, I picked this game up on a whim, its ridiculously low price sort of helped me feel comfortable picking it up. I'm very glad I did.Suits a business RPG is a role playing game where you take up the role of a businessman who just graduated from business school. Since cooperations rule the planet in this universe.For me the humor was on point and reminds me a bit of Rick and Morty, just enough dark humor and unexpected twists in it that makes it funny for me. 4th wall breaking, Easter eggs, and dark humor.Gameplay wise it reminds me of Earthbound. There is some level grinding and yes there is no free healing, however that is usually how this genre of RPG works. There is some grinding, but I never got tired of it, mostly because I kept wandering around into random peoples' houses.Usually I don't like bringing up the graphics since that is never the selling point for me, however I think it fits the dystopian 1984 vibe the developers were going for. The hand drawn backgrounds makes the game a bit more memorable in my eyes.Honestly the best part about this game besides the concept and humor is the exploration. I usually just wander around and loot everything in sight. Which leads me to discover things, I won't spoil anything since playing this game without knowing anything that pops up is satisfying.Also it is not an Undertale clone, I know my Undertale playtime isn't much, but I have played on another friend's account quite a bit to understand the gameplay and mechanics. They are similar only because of the genre they are in. 2D turn based RPGs. It is like saying every tennis video game ever conceived is a rip off of pong. Or every FPS is a ripoff of Doom. (Note: Undertale is an awesome game, I still highly recommend it, I just saw people calling this game a ripoff.)My final verdict:Suits is a good game, although humor isprobably going to fuel most of your enjoyment if you don't like the visuals or gameplay. So Suits isn't for everyone, but it is very lowly priced so honestly it is worth a shot. Plus steam refund exists now if you really really don't like the game that much.Pros:Good humorNice visualsInteresting conceptExplorationGood sound (when there is any)Isn't an Undertale ripoff like many people seem to think.Cons:Lack of soundGrindingCan be difficult for newcomers to the genre.9/10"
76561198202031650,Recommended,410670,21199023,"Posted: 13 February, 2016",all,Ryza,"Suits: A Business RPG is a unique, hilarious and clever RPG.  The player will explore a futuristic world where businesses and corporations rule the world. The story could have been fleshed out more, but the humour of the game is its redeeming quality. Suits: A Business RPG has references to many different people, things and ideas. For example, you have to rescue a rapper named 62 cents. You fight Bustin Jiebers, battle staplers, coffe mugs, ghosts, faeces, soylent meat people, Chief Ramsey. This game is just that funny.Gameplay is similar to Pokemon's turn based battle system. If battling enemies or bosses becomes too difficult, the player has a option to literally pay the enemies to lose.Suits: A Business RPG is definitely a game worth the full price."
76561198110395588,Recommended,410670,20501113,"Posted: 12 January, 2016",all,Society is screwed...,"Let me start out by noting Suits is a game inspired by OFF, a game by Mortis Ghost. In all honesty, I liked OFF a little more, but I did enjoy this game. For a dollar, it's totally worth it, even if it's only a couple hours long.The gameplay itself wasn't very inspired. I found myself using the same three strategies the entire game: Use Staple Down to disable strong, single enemies, use Staple Storm to beat groups, and attack the rest of the time. Ultimately, you should sail through it, as long as you be sure to get the best equips at all times. One interesting note is that most of your funds come from doing optional things, rather than only battling. That's pretty cool, because it gives you a reason to explore a little, even thought it's not exactly a vast world.The visuals are very unique and interesting, but if you don't love the general uniqueness, you'll likely hate it, because it's all drawn in black and white. The music is pretty good actually, though not good enough to go searching Youtube for it. Overall, I'd say these are both nice for what they are.The most important thing is the adventure, despite everything previously mentioned. The story is an interesting social commentary, with witty bits of comedy scattered through the entire game. The generallly cynical atmosphere is a great change of pace, and the whole game experience is one huge satirical parody of the greed and corruption of those in power and the mundane lives people are programmed to live, working as small cogs their whole lives for these powers. It's really frightening to have to accept this reality, but it's unfortunately accurate. People are expected to live as workers. As for the corporate and political corruption, that's all true as well, just not to a degree where society is openly a place where justice is bought, the poor are used as spare parts and people are punished for not buying things. You cannot deny that there are scandals, however. I believe the CEO of McDonald's once stated that if any of his competitors were to drown, he'd put a hose in their mouth.To wrap things up, this game is not expensive at all and a very unique experience, and I would reccommend it for those reasons."
