,Recommended,410670,21026032,"Posted: 7 February, 2016",all,stratkat,"Suits has an art style that reminds me of OFF, and it overflowing with references to games, television, and cute little bits, like putting 808 dollars in a music studio.  OFF had a much better battle theme, and more pleasant backgrounds, and what felt like a more avant garde tone.I wish it could've had a deeper meaning, I spent the last half of the game speeding through trying to find meaning behind what was happening, and came up with nothing concrete.In the game there are no women, I can't recall anyone being defined as a man either, but everyone is the same suited person, much like the famous anonymous avatar.Suits with it's references feels more like commentary on internet culture than it does on buisness/corporations.The controls are slippery, interacting with objects is often iffy, in the combat most moves are completly useless, building up TP is near impossible, even at the final boss with the best gear I couldn't build up the TP to ever use the ultimate move.  Combat never felt like a challenge, I had one KO of a party member and it was a one hit kill move.It's worth playing, if it's not a strain on your eyes, for a dollar on sale it's worth it.  I don't think I'd pay more than a dollar for a sequel."
76561198112743907,Recommended,410670,24567893,"Posted: 27 July, 2016",all,100greenmen,"Yeah this was a good game. Up front I'd say it's worth investing in if you don't mind a short little rpg.If you don't like dialouge focused games than this probably won't be your cup of tea (joe) since dialouge is the spine that keeps the game standing on it's fairly standard combat. What's nice is that it's well paced in that you don't really need to grind as long as you don't skip every encounter. Most fights are fights found throughout the world in specific areas, and there are only a few areas where random encounters even exist. It's a little rough around the edges but overall, a worthy purchase.Oh yeah, and uh, there's no way to fully restore hp without the use of a consumable item. So save whenever you can."
