,Recommended,410670,33280352,Posted: 5 July,all,FreedVoid,"Fairly entertaining game that was well worth its price. Going through the game, it reminded me of Lisa with it's weird and bizarre nuances and whips that constantly redraw in your attention. The art style at first look can be a bit dissuading to some especially with the contrast between the pixel graphics and the handmade drawings; however, it certainly does have have a charm to it that instills a unique feeling of both adoration and eeriness. The music at times was okay to listen to at times, however at others you can easily be irritated (just beeps and more beeps). Most irritating though was interacting with objects and movement. At some times, you could just interact with an object or not as other objects nearby were taking priority and movement definitely felt a bit loose. In regards to the story, it's simple yet laid out - not too complex but easy to follow - with you going from a corporate flunky to a corporate revolutionary.What there is to love most about this game is definitely the humor. As aforementioned, the game has its weird and bizarre nature, which is most explored through the dialogue. You want to interact with everything for the unexpected wits of dialogue. The media references are also in abundance as long as you can get what is being referenced, and it's a heck of a lot of fun seeing how the devs play off of everything. This gives you even MORE reason to want to check everything out for maximum enjoyment. You'll even get some achievements out of it (If you are going after these, I advise saving in a different slot after certain story points just in case you miss something).All in all, it's a bang for your buck sorta game. All you need to do is learn to not hoard healing items and use them to grind for a bit and things will play out smoothly.  It'll be fun to go through so try it out."
76561197993399611,Not Recommended,410670,33468445,Posted: 11 July,all,.iko,"Game has a lot of personality and really likeable, and I'd have given a positive review if I didn't hit a game-stopping bug halfway through. In one of the later dungeons, when it goes to load a random encounter, the game just hangs on the loading screen. This is on the mac version of the game, and I checked the forum and found other people with the same problem, on the same platform. So that sucks.The art-style is charming, and the plotting is a dystopian satire that sometimes hits and sometimes misses, loaded with lots of self-consciously goofy jokes. The raw mechanical game itself is honestly kind of bad. It's just completely bog standard RPG Maker/Dragon Warrior type stuff, and really unevenly designed. For example, you'll enter one area with lots of easy monsters that give tons of gold and experience that you can grind, but in the very next area the monsters are way harder, but give substantially less experience and gold. Just kind of screwy stuff like that. So you're mostly playing it for the world, the exploration, and the novelty."
